item.description:
For some reason, I keep finding myself writing unit tests that need to make assertions about an XML document. To keep things DRY, I&rsquo;ve packaged up my custom assertion methods as a PyPi module: unittest-xml. There&rsquo;s a small chance it may be useful to others.
Sample Usage Enable the additional assert methods using a mixin:
import unittest from xmltest import XMLAssertions class SampleTestCase(unittest.TestCase, XMLAssertions): ... Now suppose that the expected XML from some SUT1 is:
